Very usefull....

- When I add a file from my gallery called myfile.jpg, the app renames it to New Measures.jpg. You would think it would keep the same file name. - I like that it easily shows measurements on the line although it's problematic. In the app, the values get jumbled when I have the image at normal size. The only way to not see them jumbled is to view in a zoomed in size. - Although my annotations looked perfect in the app, after exporting, several of the numbers aren't even close to the line...in fact, they are switched with values for other lines so it's easy to misinterpret the actual value for the line. Exporting to a pdf instead makes no difference. The downside here is I can't click on the line to see which number belongs to it no matter if it's a jpg or pdf. This is a huge issue for us.

Just a suggestion, if you could add a lock button so when I'm done nothing gets moved or added. So I'm not going back & deleting all the arrows added in my pocket & what not. Other than that thanx for the awesome app.
